OL,3,CDog walker's wife may have heard him
OL,4,Ccalling to her before dying in Storm
OL,5,CBert
OL,7,FAt the opening of an inquest at
OL,8,FRuthin, John Gittins, senior coroner
OL,9,Ffor North Wales East and Central, said
OL,10,Fhe had been informed by North Wales
OL,11,FPolice that Mr Perry and his wife
OL,12,FCatherine set out together but he then
OL,13,Fwent on alone with the dog.
OL,15,FHe knew the area well and was wearing
OL,16,Fwaterproof clothing.
OL,18,FMr Gittins said Mrs Perry spoke to her
OL,19,Fhusband on the phone but raised the
OL,20,Falarm around 20 minutes later when she
OL,21,Fno longer had a reply.
